cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on generating images based on textual descriptions and evaluates the generated images using an object detector. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new model for text-to-image synthesis and introduces a new evaluation metric. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of generative adversarial networks and the addition of an object pathway to the generator and discriminator. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with generating images based on textual descriptions, which falls under the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with generating images and evaluating their quality, which falls under the domain of computer graphics.
